# P12-001 implementation plan (branch `feature/P12-001-remote-vfs-pgen-reads`)

Authoritative build plan for remote/VFS `.pgen` reads. Design rationale is in
`P12-001-remote-vfs-pgen-reads`; this is the how. **Milestone 1 (surface
enumeration) is done** — result below. **Milestone 3 (the range-read spike) is the
go/no-go** for the full remote path; do not polish the patch set before that number.

## Architecture — two I/O paths + a resolution front-end

Separate **path resolution** (glob / `pathmacro:` / `file_search_path` / protocol →
a concrete path) from **byte I/O** (how the bytes are pulled). Resolution is a VFS
front-end that runs for every input; I/O then takes one of two branches:

- **Path L — native/local fastpath.** `PgenFile.ff` is a raw `FILE*` (`fopen` /
  `fread_unlocked`), **byte-identical to unpatched plink2**, stdio-buffered. Serves
  BOTH (a) plain-local paths [today's behavior] and (b) paths the VFS front-end
  resolved to a **local** file [the folded-in `file_search_path`/`pathmacro:` gap].
  No per-read VFS overhead.
- **Path V — full VFS.** `PgenFile.vfs_handle` is a DuckDB `FileHandle`; the op
  wrappers use positioned `Read(buf, n, location)`. Serves **remote** paths
  (`s3://`, `https://`, …) that can't be localized. Buffering comes from
  `cache_httpfs` (or an optional block layer), never from stdio.

"plink2-native" and "local-after-resolution" are the **same L branch**, differing
only in whether the front-end had to resolve the path. The two *paths* are L and V.

### `plinking_pgen_io` policy (explicit control; default auto)

| value | behavior |
|---|---|
| `auto` *(default)* | resolve via VFS; local → **L**, remote → **V** |
| `native` | raw `fopen` only, **no VFS at all** (pristine plink2; errors on a remote/unresolvable path) — the zero-overhead / escape-hatch guarantee |
| `localize` | resolve, and **download remote → local temp**, then **L** (never per-read VFS; the safe, no-fork-needed remote strategy + the spike baseline) |
| `vfs` | always **V** (positioned reads even for local) — for testing/consistency and measuring V overhead |

`auto` gives the good default; `native` guarantees today's behavior is untouched;
`localize` is what we ship if the spike says range-reads don't win; `vfs` is the
measurement/edge mode.

### The seam (context solved by the VFS)

Path V's `FileHandle` is opened **extension-side** via
`fs.OpenFile(path, READ, ClientContextFileOpener(context))` — the opener carries
`SecretManager` → httpfs credentials + settings (confirmed: file_system.hpp:149,
file_opener.hpp:45). The handle is self-contained after open, so pgenlib's C-ABI
seam is only **`pread(handle, buf, n, off)` / `fsize(handle)` / `close(handle)`** —
no `open` callback, no context, **no DuckDB types in pgenlib**. The extension picks
L vs V at open with `IsRemoteFile` / `OnDiskFile`.

Why L must exist (not just use a local `FileHandle`): `FileHandle::Read(…,
location)` is one `pread` **syscall per call, no stdio readahead**, while pgenlib
issues ~1 read per variant record → a local sequential scan would regress to
syscall-per-record. L keeps stdio buffering; V relies on `cache_httpfs`.

## Milestone 1 RESULT — poison enumeration (done)

Poisoned the 3 read-path `FILE*` fields (`PoisonPgenFile*`) and compiled
`pgenlib_read.cc` in isolation with the CMake pgenlib flags. **34 error sites, all
in `pgenlib_read.cc`** — completeness proven by the compiler. Op vocabulary = 5:

| op | sites |
|---|---|
| open (`fopen` + assign a `FILE*` into the field) | 3 (L2067 `pgrp->ff = fopen(...)`, L709/825) |
| `fseeko` | 9 |
| `ftello` | 2 |
| `fread_unlocked` | 2 |
| `fclose_null(&field)` (pgenlib helper, `FILE**`) | 5 |
| read field into a local `FILE*` (the local + its uses convert too) | 3 |

`getc_unlocked` / `rewind` don't touch these fields (block buffer, not file). State
carrier: `PgenFile { FILE* ff; void* vfs_handle; uint64_t vfs_off; }`; the 5 op
wrappers branch on `vfs_handle != nullptr`.

## Sequenced milestones

1. **Enumerate (done).** 34 sites / 5 ops.
2. **2a — shim + local-transparent patch.** Add `PgenFile` + the 5 op wrappers
   (Path L only: `vfs_handle` always null → wrappers call libc, byte-identical).
   Patch the 34 sites. Build; **full suite must stay green** = the abstraction is a
   no-op for local. This is the safe first patch to the plink files.
3. **2b — wire Path V.** Extension opens the `FileHandle` (context), threads it into
   pgenlib (a small init addition, not an fname-signature change); wrappers' V
   branch does positioned reads. Add the `plinking_pgen_io` policy + `IsRemoteFile`/
   `OnDiskFile` selection + the `localize` (download-to-temp) strategy.
4. **3 — MEASURE (go/no-go).** Contiguous-region query, bytes fetched + wall clock,
   over a local HTTP server: `auto`/V raw httpfs vs V + `cache_httpfs` vs `localize`
   (download-to-temp). If V doesn't **decisively** beat `localize`, ship `localize`
   and keep V behind the flag. Only then invest in range-coalescing/`.pgi`/canary.

## Patch mechanism

Edits live as **re-appliable patches** to the `third_party/plink-ng` submodule
(`patches/plink-ng/*.patch`), applied idempotently at build time (precedent:
`src/musl_compat.h` force-included via CMake). Must be idempotent + CI-reproducible
from clean; minimal + one-logical-change-per-patch so they are **upstreamable**
(the `plink2_text.h:137` "network support later" comment is the open door). The
drift canary (`scripts/check_vendored_drift.sh`) treats the patch as the intended
delta. *(2a may edit the submodule directly to prove the patch, then capture as
`.patch` + CMake apply once green.)*

